# Cursor Rules for Xcode Project

## File Creation Rules
When creating new files in the project:
1. If creating a Swift file (.swift), automatically add it to the Xcode project
2. If creating a configuration file (.xcconfig), automatically add it to the Xcode project
3. If creating a property list file (.plist), automatically add it to the Xcode project
4. If creating a strings file (.strings), automatically add it to the Xcode project
5. If creating an entitlements file (.entitlements), automatically add it to the Xcode project

## Project Structure
- Keep files organized in appropriate groups
- Use meaningful file names
- Follow Swift naming conventions
- Add files to the correct target

## Build Configuration
- Use Debug.xcconfig for debug builds
- Use Release.xcconfig for release builds
- Maintain consistent build settings across configurations

## File Types
- Swift files: sourcecode.swift
- Configuration files: text.xcconfiguration
- Property lists: text.plist.xml
- String files: text.plist.strings
- Entitlements: text.plist.entitlements
- Storyboards: file.storyboard
- XIB files: file.xib
- Asset catalogs: folder.assetcatalog
- Data models: wrapper.xcdatamodel
- Font files: file

## Automation
- Run add_files_to_xcode.sh when new files are created
- Update project.pbxproj automatically
- Generate unique UUIDs for new file references
- Add files to appropriate build phases 